<h4 align="center">MARIJUANA AS A &quot;HOLY SACRAMENT&quot;: IS
THE<br>
USE OF PEYOTE CONSTITUTIONALLY<br>
DISTINGUISHABLE FROM THAT OF<br>
MARIJUANA IN BONA FIDE<br>
RELIGIOUS CEREMONIES?<br>
Cynthia S. Mazur*<br>
NOTRE DAME JOURNAL OF LAW, ETHICS &amp; PUBLIC POLICY<br>
Volume 5, Issue No. 3, 1991<br>
pages 693-727</h4>

<h4><img src="../../images/reddot.gif" width="14" height="14"> <a
href="mazur1.html">Marijuana as a Holy Sacrament (Part 1)</a> </h4>

<h4><img src="../../images/reddot.gif" width="14" height="14"> <a
href="mazur2.html">Marijuana as a Holy Sacrament (Part 2)</a> </h4>

